# Icons Directory

Store custom icons and SVG graphics here.

## Current Structure

```
icons/
├── README.md (this file)
```

## Adding Icons

Place SVG or PNG icon files here:

```
icons/
├── graduation-cap.svg
├── music-icon.svg
├── location-icon.svg
└── calendar-icon.svg
```

## Emoji vs Custom Icons

This project primarily uses **Unicode emoji** for simplicity:
- 🎓 Graduation cap
- 🎵 Music note
- 📍 Location pin
- 📅 Calendar
- 💌 Envelope
- ✨ Sparkles

### Why Emoji?

- ✅ No extra HTTP requests
- ✅ Works on all devices
- ✅ Built into all fonts
- ✅ Smaller project size
- ✅ Easy to maintain

### Custom Icons

If you want to use custom SVG icons:

1. **Create or download SVG** icons
2. **Place in this directory**
3. **Reference in HTML:**
   ```html
   <img src="assets/icons/graduation-cap.svg" alt="Graduation">
   ```

## Recommended Icon Sets

- **Heroicons:** https://heroicons.com/ (Free, beautiful)
- **Feather Icons:** https://feathericons.com/ (Minimal)
- **FontAwesome:** https://fontawesome.com/ (Comprehensive)
- **Material Icons:** https://material.io/icons/ (Google)

## SVG Best Practices

```svg
<!-- Always include viewBox for scalability -->
<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor">
  <!-- SVG content -->
</svg>
```

## Performance Notes

- SVG icons are scalable and small
- PNG icons are raster (fixed size)
- Embed small SVGs inline in CSS (avoid HTTP requests)
- Use `loading="lazy"` for image icons

## File Size Guidelines

- SVG icons: < 5KB each
- PNG icons: < 20KB each
- Total icons directory: < 500KB

Start with emoji - add custom icons only if needed! 🎨
